President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Sarah Elizabeth Mendelson as the Representative of the United States on the Economic and Social Council of the United Nations, with the rank of Ambassador. Mendelson is currently the Senior Adviser and Director of the Human Rights Initiative at the Center for Strategic and International Studies. 

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Peter J. Beshar as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars. Beshar is currently the Executive Vice President and General Counsel of the Marsh & McLennan Companies.

Additionally, President Obama intends to appoint Kathryn Brinsfield as the Assistant Secretary for Health Affairs and Chief Medical Officer at the Department of Homeland Security. Brinsfield currently serves as the Associate Chief Medical Officer and Director for Workforce Health and Medical Support at DHS.

Allen Croff will be appointed as a member of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board. Croff is currently an adjunct professor at Vanderbilt University and a consultant to the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board.

Lastly, President Obama intends to appoint Todd McCracken as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. McCracken is currently the President and CEO of the National Small Business Association.